race.comment: MAMMA MIA (12) went well at Kembla Grange on debut then progressed nicely beaten 2L here over 1200m at this track. Maps well and the in-form Collett sticks aboard. Steps up to the longer sprint and she's ready to win. SO REBELLIOUS (5) resumed with a decent effort at Goulburn over this distance. He has more to give and a bold showing is expected with added fitness. Wary of BEAUTY SWIFT (3), who debuts for a smart Sydney yard with the blinkers on. Was an easy Hawkesbury trail winner and jumps from the rails gate. The betting will be key. Doubtland filly CHAITHNIA (10) has shown enough at the trials to to be competitive on debut so keep safe.
